OL,6,FIn the Royal Court, the victim decided
OL,7,Fto read out her own impact statement:
OL,8,F"I was silenced, and I was too scared
OL,9,Fto speak out and stop it.
OL,11,F"I have struggled to come to terms
OL,12,Fwith what has happened to me (...) I
OL,13,Fstill have the image of that
OL,14,Fterrifying and dangerous man, and I
OL,15,Ftruly believe he will come back at any
OL,16,Fmoment."
